<body>

  <h1>Privacy Policy for Bayaan</h1>

  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 22 December 2025</p>

  <p>
    Bayaan (“we,” “us,” or “our”) values your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we
    collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use the Bayaan mobile
    application (the “App”).
  </p>

  <p>
    By accessing or using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information
    in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

  <h3>A. Information You Provide</h3>
  <p>
    We collect limited personal information that you voluntarily provide and that is
    necessary to deliver the App’s core functionality, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email address (for account access, authentication, and support)</li>
    <li>User preferences, including:
      <ul>
        <li>Salah calculation method</li>
        <li>Madhab preference</li>
        <li>Prayer time adjustments</li>
        <li>Notification settings</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do <strong>not</strong> collect phone numbers.
  </p>

  <h3>B. Location Information</h3>
  <p>
    Bayaan uses location information solely to calculate accurate Salah timings.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Location may be provided manually by selecting a city or region</li>
    <li>Or obtained through device location services with your explicit permission</li>
    <li>Only approximate location is used</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Location data is not used for tracking, profiling, or advertising purposes.
    You may disable location access at any time, though this may impact prayer time accuracy.
  </p>

  <h3>C. Automatically Collected Information</h3>
  <p>
    To ensure app reliability and performance, we may automatically collect limited
    technical information, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Device type and operating system</li>
    <li>App version</li>
    <li>Crash reports and basic usage analytics</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This information is aggregated and does not directly identify you.
  </p>

  <h3>D. Advertising Identifiers (Future Provision)</h3>
  <p>
    Bayaan does not currently display advertisements.
  </p>
  <p>
    If advertising is introduced in the future:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Non-personal advertising identifiers (such as Android Advertising ID or iOS IDFA)
        may be used</li>
    <li>Advertising will comply with applicable privacy and data protection laws</li>
    <li>Users will be provided any required consent or opt-out options</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>
    We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>To calculate and display accurate Salah timings</li>
    <li>To personalize prayer notifications and app behavior</li>
    <li>To operate, maintain, and improve the App</li>
    <li>To respond to user inquiries and provide customer support</li>
    <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
    <li>To enable optional future features, including advertising if introduced</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information.
  </p>

  <p>
    We may share limited information only in the following circumstances:
  </p>

  <h3>Service Providers</h3>
  <p>
    Trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App
    (such as analytics or hosting services), under strict confidentiality obligations.
  </p>

  <h3>Legal Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    When required to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes,
    or to protect the rights, safety, and property of Bayaan and its users.
  </p>

  <h3>Advertising Partners (Future)</h3>
  <p>
    If advertising is implemented in the future, limited data may be shared with
    advertising partners in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable laws,
    and only where user consent is required and obtained.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to provide the App’s
    services, fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, or comply with
    legal obligations.
  </p>
  <p>
    Users may request deletion of their personal information at any time.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>5. Your Privacy Rights and Choices</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have the right to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access your personal information</li>
    <li>Correct or update inaccurate information</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your information</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent for location access</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise these rights, please contact us using the details below.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Bayaan is not intended for children under the age of 13.
    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
    If such information is identified, it will be deleted promptly.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures
    to protect your information. However, no method of transmission or storage is
    completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
    Material changes will be communicated through the App or other appropriate means.
    Continued use of the App after changes indicates acceptance of the updated policy.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices,
    please contact us:
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong> info@bayaanapp.com<br>
    <strong>Address:</strong> Ontario, Canada
  </p>

